Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20this%20focus%20on%20culture%2C%20we%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fjoel.is%2Fpost%2F37639846554%2Fthe-evolution-of-culture-at-a-startup%22%3Edone%20quite%20a%20few%20things%20rather%20early%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Buffer.%20We%20started%20to%20think%20seriously%20about%20culture%20when%20we%20were%20just%207%20people%20and%20put%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.slideshare.net%2Fbufferapp%2Fbuffer-culture-03%22%3Eour%20values%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20words%20shortly%20afterwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EA%20realization%20my%20co-founder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fleowid%22%3ELeo%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20I%20had%20shortly%20after%20this%20was%20that%20if%20we%20truly%20want%20to%20focus%20on%20creating%20a%20great%20culture%2C%20it%20is%20inevitable%20that%20some%20people%20won%E2%80%99t%20work%20out%20and%20we%20would%20have%20to%20ask%20them%20to%20leave%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20very%20little%20written%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20firing%20people%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20hard%20thing%20to%20talk%20about%2C%20especially%20when%20you%20are%20still%20small.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.inc.com%2Fjeff-haden%2Finside-buffer-company-complete-transparency.html%22%3Eone%20of%20our%20highest%20cultural%20values%20is%20transparency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20for%20some%20time%20I%20have%20felt%20we%20were%20not%20being%20true%20to%20our%20values%20by%20not%20talking%20about%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ch3%20id%3D%22thejourneytothecurrentbufferteam%22%3EThe%20journey%20to%20the%20current%20Buffer%20team%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3ETo%20put%20things%20in%20perspective%20here%3A%20Buffer%20is%20now%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fjoel.is%2Fpost%2F59525266381%2Fthe-joys-and-benefits-of-working-as-a-distributed-team%22%3Eteam%20of%2013%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20in%20the%20journey%20so%20far%20we%E2%80%99ve%20actually%20let%206%20people%20go.%20For%20us%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20luckily%20never%20had%20financial%20struggles%2C%20all%20of%20these%20decisions%20were%20based%20around%20culture-fit.%20It%E2%80%99s%20hard%20work%20to%20hire%20people%20and%20even%20harder%20to%20fire%20people%2C%20so%20a%20team%20of%2013%20feels%20rather%20small%20for%20the%20efforts%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20through%20so%20far.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20this%20team%20of%2013%20is%20a%20real%20privilege%20to%20be%20part%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ch3%20id%3D%22hiringforskillsvshiringforculture%22%3EHiring%20for%20skills%20vs%20hiring%20for%20culture%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20Buffer%2C%20I%20had%20no%20real%20idea%20what%20culture%20is.%20We%20grew%20quite%20fast%2C%20and%20my%20intuition%20was%20to%20fill%20the%20gaps%20we%20had%20with%20the%20most%20skilled%20people%20I%20could%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20reached%207%20people%2C%20I%20started%20to%20see%20the%20importance%20of%20building%20a%20cohesive%20team%20that%20works%20well%20together%20and%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20fun%20to%20be%20part%20of.%20A%20large%20part%20of%20this%20is%20defining%20the%20culture%20and%20finding%20people%20who%20are%20a%20great%20fit%20for%20that%20culture.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20we%20put%20our%20culture%20into%20words%20and%20created%20our%20cultural%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20had%20put%20our%20culture%20into%20words%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20when%20we%20started%20to%20much%20more%20rigorously%20hire%20based%20on%20the%20values.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20really%20hard%20to%20hire%20for%20culture-fit%20until%20you%20have%20your%20values%20in%20words%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cblockquote%3E%0A%20%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98Cultural%20Fit%E2%80%99%20is%20only%20a%20valid%20hiring%20criteria%20if%20you%20can%20accurately%20define%20your%20culture%E2%80%9D%20-%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fchrisyeh.blogspot.com%2F2013%2F09%2Fcultural-fit-is-only-valid-hiring.html%22%3EChris%20Yeh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EWith%20our%20culture%20in%20place%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20evolved%20our%20hiring%20process%20and%20we%20focus%20a%20lot%20on%20the%20culture%20we%20have.%20This%20means%20finding%20people%20who%20are%20positive%20and%20happy%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20self-improvement%2C%20who%20have%20gratitude%2C%20are%20humble%20and%20are%20comfortable%20with%20our%20extreme%20transparency.%20We%20have%20what%20we%20call%20a%20%E2%80%98Buffer%20Bootcamp%E2%80%99%2C%20essentially%20a%2045%20day%20contract%20period%20with%201%3A1%20meetings%20for%20feedback%20at%202%20weeks%2C%201%20month%20and%2045%20days.%20A%20lot%20of%20this%20is%20to%20see%20whether%20Buffer%20is%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20the%20person%20joining%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20more%20rigorous%20process%2C%20we%20found%20that%20some%20people%20didn%E2%80%99t%20fit%20the%20culture%20and%20letting%20people%20go%20was%20inevitable.%20Surprisingly%2C%20the%20very%20act%20of%20letting%20people%20go%20has%20shaped%20our%20culture%20more%20than%20anything%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cblockquote%3E%0A%20%20%3Cp%3E%22I%20think%20some%20of%20the%20core%20decisions%20that%20impact%20culture%20are%20who%20you%20let%20on%20the%20bus%20and%20who%20you%20make%20sure%20gets%20off%20the%20bus.%20The%20values%20that%20determine%20these%20decisions%20really%20shape%20your%20culture.%20Similarly%2C%20who%20gets%20rewarded%20and%20promoted%20within%20your%20company%20really%20shapes%20your%20culture.%20So%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20actual%20every%20day%20operating%20decisions%20that%20most%20shape%20your%20culture.%22%20-%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DLn-B_fs9QMY%22%3EDave%20Kashen%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%0A%0A%3Ch3%20id%3D%22cultureisnotaboutrightorwrong%22%3ECulture%20is%20not%20about%20right%20or%20wrong%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EAlthough%20we%E2%80%99ve%20let%206%20people%20go%2C%20these%20were%20all%20great%20people%20and%20they%20all%20did%20fantastic%20work.%20We%20just%20realized%20that%20they%20were%20not%20a%20perfect%20fit%20for%20our%20culture%2C%20so%20it%20made%20sense%20to%20part%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EI%20would%20even%20go%20a%20step%20further%20and%20say%20that%20keeping%20people%20around%20who%20are%20not%20a%20great%20culture-fit%20is%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20things%20that%20could%20happen%20to%20someone.%20It%20has%20almost%20always%20been%20a%20mutual%20feeling%20when%20I%20had%20the%20conversation%20to%20let%20someone%20go%3A%20they%20felt%20some%20relief.%20I%20even%20have%20this%20quote%20on%20my%20wall%20to%20remind%20myself%20to%20think%20in%20this%20way%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cblockquote%3E%0A%20%20%3Cp%3E%22Waiting%20too%20long%20before%20acting%20is%20equally%20unfair%20to%20the%20people%20who%20need%20to%20get%20off%20the%20bus.%20For%20every%20minute%20you%20allow%20a%20person%20to%20continue%20holding%20a%20seat%20when%20you%20know%20that%20person%20will%20not%20make%20it%20in%20the%20end%2C%20youre%20stealing%20a%20portion%20of%20his%20life%2C%20time%20that%20he%20could%20spend%20finding%20a%20better%20place%20where%20he%20could%20flourish.%22%20-%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0058DRUV6%2Fref%3Dr_soa_w_d%22%3EJim%20Collins%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%0A%0A%3Ch3%20id%3D%22whylettingpeoplegoispartoftheprocess%22%3EWhy%20letting%20people%20go%20is%20part%20of%20the%20process%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EI%20think%20firing%20someone%20is%20perhaps%20one%20of%20the%20hardest%20things%20you%20have%20to%20learn%20as%20a%20founder.%20Another%20key%20realization%20for%20me%20has%20been%20that%20letting%20people%20go%20is%20a%20continual%20part%20of%20growing%20a%20great%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20how%20awesome%20our%20hiring%20process%20is%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20inevitable%20that%20sometimes%20the%20person%20is%20not%20a%20great%20fit.%20Now%20that%20we%20have%20grown%20to%2013%20people%20and%20had%20to%20make%20tough%20team%20changes%20along%20the%20way%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20started%20to%20see%20a%20ratio%20emerge.%20We%20now%20know%20not%20to%20be%20surprised%20if%20about%201%20in%204%20people%20we%20hire%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work%20out.%20It%20helps%20to%20know%20this%20possibility%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cblockquote%3E%0A%20%20%3Cp%3E%22If%20you%20are%20super-scrupulous%20about%20your%20hiring%20process%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20still%20have%20maybe%20a%2070%25%20success%20rate%20of%20a%20new%20person%20really%20working%20out%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20lucky.%22%20-%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fpandawhale.com%2Fpost%2F17923%2Fhow-to-hire-the-best-people-youve-ever-worked-with-pmarca-archive%22%3EMarc%20Andreessen%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20probably%20one%20of%20the%20hardest%20areas%20of%20learning%20I%E2%80%99ve%20experienced%20as%20a%20CEO.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20last%2010%20months%20thinking%20this%20through%2C%20reading%20as%20much%20as%20I%20could%20about%20it%20and%20getting%20lots%20of%20advice.%20We%E2%80%99re%20still%20at%20the%20very%20beginning%2C%20but%20it%20is%20comforting%20to%20have%20got%20to%20a%20point%20where%20this%20is%20a%20bit%20less%20scary.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20had%20to%20let%20people%20go%20while%20building%20your%20company%3F%20What%20do%20you%20think%20about%20the%20priority%20which%20should%20be%20placed%20on%20culture-fit%3F%20I%E2%80%99d%20love%20to%20hear%20your%20thoughts%20on%20this%20topic.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20special%20thanks%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLeoWid%22%3ELeo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCaroKopp%22%3ECarolyn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBelleBethCooper%22%3EBelle%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsunils34%22%3ESunil%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20reading%20drafts%20of%20this.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EPhoto%20credit%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.flickr.com%2Fphotos%2Fka